				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">/Sigh sadly the grounds for this .... "stand down" 40 pages of ..... posts is based partly on fallacy. A paladin tanked a potime god !!! oh no !! the horror !! and an Enchanter could probably tank Ssra lvl named...... Its a simple fact of EQ that the mudflation will make more people be able to do more things and trvialize previous content.
<br />

<br />
It was only a matter of time before paladins and Sk's started tanking Time mobs. As they got better armor, hps, ac, etc.... Recall that a warrior was the first to tank these mobs down for a reason.... Warriors with defensive HAVE better dmg mitigation.....Warriors are NOT all of a sudden tanking "worse" because knights and monks are tanking the same mobs now....
<br />

<br />
Which in my opinion is the simple fix for Warriors........ at least in my humble opinion.... Make defensive 50% innate........ and 75% activateable.... yes this makes defensive 25% better then it was when fully activated. 
<br />

<br />
This does a few things .... One it allows Sony to make mobs that only Warriors can tank. Two it makes it so in general situations a warrior will always be a better melee sponge even without a disc. Three it improves warriors in raids and in exp groups allowing the "holy trinity" group to be less of a necessity... what cant find a cleric? ahhh no problem grab a druid and a warrior with their innate dmg mitigation druid heals could keep up. Fourth, it allows a warrior to actually USE there other discs instead of being taunt taunt taunt /disc defensive, taunt taunt taunt, boring tripe's. Honestly a warriors class role in "MY" opinion is to be a dmg sponge... so why shouldnt they BE the best dmg sponges.... and i dont mean relying 100% of the time on a silly disc that lasts a few minutes to accomplish this. 
<br />

<br />
This one fix actually would fix a lot of problems and its simple, but heck no one asked me........and im sure someone would still piss and moan about it.
<br />

