			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Grumsh wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">A paladin tanked a potime god</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
   Actually, according to one guilds web site they used a Monk to tank Terris Thule and Sarryn.
<br />

<br />
   While, initially, you solution looks good, it really doesn't respond to the core problems of the Warrior / Monk / Rogue classes as they currently stand.
<br />

<br />
   As I understand it there are 3 major issues that these three classes have right now.  Of course when you read their sites, they, like every other class have people wanting eyebeam lasers and the ability to insta-kill Kyrfym, but I tend to ignore those ones.
<br />

<br />
   1.  Warrior Taunt - IMO this is quite possibly the biggest issue so far.  As it currently stands, it really is better to have a non-warrior tank in XP groups for the simple fact that all other DPS members have to throttle back their DPS with a Warrior tanking.  Further, the time it takes for a Warrior to generate sufficient hate is somewhere around 6 - 8 times what it takes for a SK, Pally, or Ranger to generate the same amount of hate.
<br />

<br />
   2.  Utility / Versatility vs DPS - At one time each of these three classes had a very well defined function / role in the group or raid beyond simple DPS and damage absorbtion.  Unfortunately with the release of SoL, their role / function has become infringed upon, or even surpassed by other class, without a significant alteration in their DPS or damage absorption capabilities to compensate.
<br />

<br />
   3.  Group / Raid Desirability - At present, these three classes are fairly low on the desirability chart for many XP groups, and almost as low on most raids due mostly to issue number 2 above.
<br />

<br />
   Personally, I can see a lot of their points, and unfortunately PoP and LDoN have exagerated these points greatly.  It is at the point now, for me personally, that I will gladly take a Pally or SK over a Warrior in any XP group, and will generally pick a Chanter / Wizard over a Monk or Rogue in the same groups.
<br />

<br />
   In addition, as has been proven by a couple guilds of later, Warriors, Monks, and Rogues really aren't required on many raids any longer.  This is due a great deal to the current itemization issues, but also due in large par to the way the AA's work.
<br />

<br />
   Finally, to many people, this has gone on long enough.  SoE has stated for close to a year now that they are working on melee balancing, however, at the fan faire, they actually came out and said 'Oh, no, we are not really working on it yet'.  To many of the pure melee's this was a serious slap in the face, considering the boost that hybrids recieved with the release of PoP.<br />_________________<br /><ul><li><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=67241">Elder Kaatt</a>, Sixty-Five Year Old Khati Sha Feral Lord of Xev.<ul><li>BST65.254/Xv h++ 4(3.8)khp 4.1km ft5 r10 !G&gt;++++ e++ o T++ L++ H- f+ g b !t D+ X@</ul><li><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=362220">Aaeorm</a>, Enchantement Technician of the Sixty-Second Tier of Xev.<ul><li>ENC62.1/Xv h-- 1.5(1.7)khp 3.3km ft1 r3 !G&gt;++++ e+&gt;++++ o T++ L-- H- f+ g b(@) c+&gt;++++ t-&gt;! D+ X@</ul><li><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=337255">Investigator Aaeorn</a>, Fifty-Fifth Circle Redeemed Thief Catcher of Xev.<ul><li>ROG55/Xv h 1.4(1.6)khp !m ft1 r3 !G e o T++ !L H- f+++ g !b !c !t D+ X@</ul></ul></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
