			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Changing classes abilities in either ways up or down (more abilities or nerf) is a pure waste of time in a game like EQ : its been created long ago, its an old game, and people got used to see every class in a special way, so that even changes wont persuade other classes to immediatly change their point of view about it.
<br />

<br />
Warriors are tanks, high AC, medium mitigation, medium dps, supposely high aggro.
<br />
Paladins are holy tanks, that means they are warriors AND have special divine abilities (partial heals, stun, bonus on undeads) which come directly from their Good Aligned God.
<br />
SKs are evil tanks, once called master of battles, that means they are warriors AND have special evil abilities (lifetaps HPs/mana, partial dots, FD) which come directly from their Evil aligned God.
<br />

<br />
Nerfing a class or boosting another has no more value nowadays, as classes are too intrigated one in each others.
<br />

<br />
Giving special abilities to warriors can be a solution, but on the long term, its just another thing that will take A LONG TIME to come in everyone's mind : remember how long it took for the BST to be understood by other people and accepted ? Most of you know that, you used to be CLE, SHM, MNK, WARR, and you made a BST WHEN you realized what they were able to make in groups, solo or raids. Before that, you were looking sadly at us BST when we were LFG for hours and been replied over and over that our dps sucks or that you prefer getting a MNK instead. ONE WHOLE YEAR at least has been needed to change poeple point of view about BST.
<br />

<br />
Change warriors and it will take 6 months for people to understand it, and you will still see "grab a pally instead" or "i want an SK as a tank plz" ... And in my opinion, in 6 months, well, EQ1 is dead : EQ2, Horizons, World of Warcraft, Final Fantasy, Star Wars galaxy, DaoC, UO, Anarchy Online, well there will be dozens of games with better graphical or technical engines behind that will see EQ1 with at least 50% of its population leaving. With EQ2 coming up soon, i dont see Sony working hard on any class balance or major changes.
<br />

<br />
I always thought that there is only 2 ways of dealing with these class balances issues :
<br />

<br />
1- One character = One class = one ability ONLY eg warriors taunt, paladins make holy damages on every mobs with special 1HS, SKs make huge but slow dam with 2HS, clerics heal, shamans debuff, monks pull, rogues BS, etc etc
<br />

<br />
In AD&D, this exists well and the bonus of being a unique class is a boost in the xp gaining
<br />

<br />
2- One character = multiclasses but slower xp eg the more classes you are experiencing (no limitations, what for ?) the less xp you gain. But unique abilities stay restricted to the primary class.
<br />

<br />
That seems to be tested in Final Fantasy atm.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=258387" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://c.revol.free.fr/sig.JPG" border="0" /></a>
<br />
The Nameless</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
