			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">XP penalties wont work in a finite level system like EQ
<br />

<br />
Why?
<br />

<br />
Cause sooner or later the monk warrior wizard cleric wil hit 65 as well - and no on eelse will get a look in
<br />

<br />
And then the (all classes) dude will hit 65 - and people will all be exactly the same.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Systems like SWG where multi classing is open, but you have a finite total to achieve is one way
<br />

<br />

<br />
Systems like FF on line where multi classing is limited to 1 secondary job is OK because everyone has the same limit.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Open ended systems (not that I can think of one) can freely have multi classing.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Anyway - class balance IS important in a MMORPG simply because everyone will want to play their favorite type of character, and everyone will want to be at the very least a competitive choice for that group slot.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
